CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 1, 1950, pg. 17 reads: "Omegas Induct Editor - Members of Iota Phi (graduate) Chapter of Omega Psi Phi Fraternity, Pittsburgh, Saturday evening inducted another nationally prominent leader when William G. Nunn, managing editor of The Pittsburgh Courier, was initiated in Steel City. Left to right, kneeling, are James A. Roberts, Gene Williams, Igal Spraggins and Frank Lavalle.  Standing, second row: Mansfield Coles, J.D. Lewis, Oliver L. Johnson, Albert Brown, Council Buchanan, William G. Nunn, Paul F. Jones, Luther W. Trice, deputy district representative; Theodore W. Graham, Harry Conrad Jr., and Charles Watkins Back row: Andrew Coles, Olympia Lowe, basileus; Robert Woodruff, Frank Clark and Earl Brooks. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait kneeling, from left: James A. Roberts, Gene Williams, Igal Spraggins, Frank Lavelle; standing, second row: Mansfield Coles, J. D. Lewis, Oliver L. Johnson, Albert Brown, Council Buchanan, William G. Nunn, Paul F. Jones, Luther W. Trice, Theodore W. Graham, Harry Conrad Jr., and Charles Watkins; back row, left to right: Andrew Coles, Olympia Lowe, Robert Woodruff, Frank Clark, and Earl Brooks, gathered in hallway with Omega Psi Phi fraternity plaque and paddle
